                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc> The name of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13357Batha"><t:roleName xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="title">Wayzaro</t:roleName> Batḫā</persName> is written in pencil in the
                              lower margin of <locus target="#2r"/>, the name of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13357Batha"><t:roleName xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="title">Wayzaro</t:roleName>
                                 Ḍaḥaytu</persName> on <locus target="#3v"/>.</desc>
                        </item>

                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc> Writing exercises in different hands were executed on <locus target="#1r #2v #3r #3v #40v"/>, of the orders of the labiovelar
                              characters <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኰ</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጐ</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቈ</foreign>,
                              and <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኰ</foreign> on <locus target="#1r"/>.
                              Rough sketch of an ornamental band in pen on <locus target="#1v #41r"/>.</desc>
                        </item>

                        <item xml:id="e4">
                           <desc> A sticker of the monastic library with the signature ‘Ms 38’ is
                              glued onto the inner side of the front board. The signature Et III is
                              written in pencil in the upper margin of <locus target="#1r"/>. The
                              inventory number 50435 is written in pencil on <locus target="#40r"/>.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>

                  <bindingDesc>
                     
                     <binding contemporary="false" xml:id="binding">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Two<material key="wood">wooden</material> boards
                           covered with tooled dark reddish-brown <material key="leather"/>, textile
                           inlays.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="wood"/>
                           <material key="leather"/>
                           <material key="textile"/>
                        </decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Cover" color="reddish-brown">Skilled
                           blind-tooling decoration on the boards: two frames with a cross inside,
                           the turn-ins and the edges are carefully tooled with lines forming
                           crosses and double circles.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="SewingStations">6 (The original binding showed
                           only two sewing stations. The Ms received additional four sewing stations
                           during the restoration process (<ref target="#condition"/>).</decoNote>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
               </physDesc>

               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate notBefore="1700" notAfter="1899" evidence="lettering"/> The earliest
                     date of production—taking into account the handwriting—can be set to the
                     eighteenth century. The name of <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13232EhetaMar">ʾƎḫǝta Māryām</persName> is mentioned in a few supplication formulas
                     following the phrase <foreign xml:lang="gez">አመትኪ፡</foreign> ‘your maid’. This
                     person was most probably the owner of the manuscript.</origin>
               </history>

